&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equality, Diversity &amp; Inclusion (EDI) Project Manager – (Temporary)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agenda for Change Band 7 or 8a based on experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time (37.5 hours/week) for 6 months Fixed-Term&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Equality, Diversity &amp; Inclusion (EDI) Project Manager to support the EDI agenda across the Herefordshire &amp; Worcestershire STP. Hosted by Wye Valley NHS Trust the successful individual will work with EDI Groups and staff Networks to shape and drive cultural change in order to create an inclusive workplace where diversity is reflected at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role provides an exceptional opportunity for an experienced EDI professional to make a positive contribution to the EDI agenda across Herefordshire &amp; Worcestershire. You will be required to establish effective working relationships with senior managers and build strategic partnerships with EDI experts and use best practice evidence to promote EDI.You will lead on developing the strategic EDI work plan for the STP and will work across organisations to embed inclusion into working cultures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drawing on expert knowledge of EDI best practice, you will offer creative and innovative ideas to support the agenda. Working closely with the STP BAME Group, You will be highly knowledgeable about EDI practices with a track record of delivering successful EDI projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to being an inclusive employer and we are happy to consider flexible working arrangements. We would welcome applications from candidates who are seeking to make a real difference to the EDI agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss the role please contact Geoffrey Etule, HR Director, Wye Valley NHS Trust on 07828 630569 or via email; geoffrey.etule@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date:&lt;/strong&gt; Wednesday 20th November 2020&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Interviews will take place Via Video:&lt;/strong&gt; Tuesday 1st December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
